  f <- dfQuadsFilt %>% filter(SITE == site) %>% pull(COUNT)
  res <- chisq.test(f)
  print(paste("Chi-squared goodness-of-fit test of Poisson distribution: ", site))
  print(res)
}

descTransect <- dfQuads %>%
  filter(
    dfQuads['DIVISION.FAMILY'] == "Phaeophyta" ) %>%
  group_by(
    YEAR, MONTH, DAY, SITE, TRANSECT, COMMON.NAME ) %>%
  summarise(
    MEAN = round(mean(COUNT), 2),
    SD = round(sd(COUNT), 2),
    SE = round(sd(COUNT)/sqrt(n()), 2),
    SUM = sum(COUNT),
    N = n(),
    .groups = 'drop' ) %>%
  arrange(
    SITE, TRANSECT, YEAR, MONTH
  )

# Use Student t test to get CI of sum observations per year/site 
for (site in unique(kelpSumFilt$SITE)) {  
  x <- kelpSumFilt %>% filter(SITE == site) %>% pull(COUNT)

  print(paste(site, "Support: x = ", length(x)))
  print(t.test(x))
}

# check correlation between years
kelpCountBySiteAndYear <- dfQuadsFilt %>% group_by(
    SITE, YEAR ) %>%
  summarise(
    MEAN = mean(COUNT),
    SD = sd(COUNT),
    .groups = 'drop'
  )
kelpCountBySiteAndYear$YEAR <- as.factor(kelpCountBySiteAndYear$YEAR)
# install.packages("tidyverse")
# library(tidyr)
kelpYearPivot <- kelpCountBySiteAndYear %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = YEAR, values_from = c(MEAN, SD)) %>%
  mutate_if(
  is.numeric, replace_na, replace = 0)


corTestResult <- cor.test(x = kelpYearPivot$MEAN_2014, y = kelpYearPivot$MEAN_2015, method = "pearson")
print(corTestResult)

# Run Poisson MLE fit
# Run Poisson Exact Test
for (site in unique(dfQuadsFilt$SITE)) {  

  x = dfQuadsFilt %>% filter(SITE == site & dfQuadsFilt$YEAR == 2014) %>% pull(COUNT)
  y = dfQuadsFilt %>% filter(SITE == site & dfQuadsFilt$YEAR == 2018) %>% pull(COUNT)
  
  if (length(x) == 0 | length(y) == 0) {
    next
  }
  
  xp <- fitdistr(x, "poisson")
  xci <- round(c(xp$estimate + c(-1,1) * 1.96 * xp$sd), 2)
  xl <- round(xp$estimate[[1]], 2)
  
  yp <- fitdistr(y, "poisson")
  yci <- round(c(yp$estimate + c(-1,1) * 1.96 * yp$sd), 2)
  yl <-round(yp$estimate[[1]], 2)
  
  print(paste(site, "Support: x = ", length(x), " y = ", length(y)))
  print(paste("x rate = ", xl, "CI(", xci[[1]], xci[[2]], ") y rate = ", yl, "CI(", yci[[1]], yci[[2]], ")"))
  
  pois <- poisson.test(x = ceiling(xl), r = yl, alternative = "greater")
  print(pois)
  # smaller event rate CI calculation using:
  # https://stats.stackexchange.com/questions/401754/determining-confidence-interval-with-one-observation-for-poisson-distribution
  pxciu <- pois[[1]] + 2 + 1.96*sqrt(pois[[1]]+1)
  pxcil <- pois[[1]] + 2 - 1.96*sqrt(pois[[1]]+1)
}
